# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
1. find target sum of `n` using given variables
2. use the largest number possible to get us close to our target using the given length
3. increment values by 1 until we have reached our target

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N)

- Space complexity: O(N)

# Code
```
func missingRolls(rolls []int, mean int, n int) []int {
    m := 0
    length := len(rolls) + n
    // total is what the sum of n + m should be
    total := mean * length

    // get the sum of rolls aka m
    for i := 0; i < len(rolls); i++ {
        m += rolls[i]
    }

    // target is our target sum of n
    target := total - m
    part := target / n
    sum := 0
    ans := make([]int, n)

    // if our fraction is smaller or larger than a die
    // its impossible
    if part < 1 || part > 6 {
        return []int{}
    }

    for i := 0; i < len(ans); i++ {
        sum += part
        ans[i] = part
    }

    i := 0

    // increment dice by 1 until we reach our target n
    for sum < target {
        for i < len(ans) && ans[i] == 6 {
            i++
        }

