# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Here if we just consider the formula of mean (mean = sum of k no. / k) and consider that the dice number is always between 1-6 then this problem can be solved easily.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
* Here we first find the sum of the required answer vector by formula:-
sum = (mean*(n+rolls.size())) - (sum of evry umbers of rolls vector).
* Then we just check the condition, if ,sum is less than n OR sum is greater than n*6 , then just return the empty vector.
* Check if the sum is perfectly divisible by n then just add it to the vector.
* And if Sum%n is not zero then after assigning Sum/nto every element we will left with Sum%n.So assign 1 to Sum%n elements of new array .

