Mean = sum(array1) + sum(array2)/array1.Length + array2.Length

# Approach
We know that mean = sum(nArr) + sum(mArr) / (nArr.Length + mArr.Length)
Therefore to get the sum(nArr) we just make it the subject of the above formula => (nArr.Length + mArr.Length) * mean - sum(mArr)
Then to get the values of nArr, we take the sum(nArr)/nArr.Length continuously while subtracting the value from it

