# Approach
1) Initialize variable sum as 0 and add the elements of the vector rolls in the sum using for loop.
2) Initialize variable rem to what should be thetotal sum of the missing elements
3) If the rem is less than no of elements that mean a missing element should be less than 1 which is not possible and if rem is greater than 6 * no of elements that means a missing element should be greater than 6 which is not possible so in both cases return empty vector
4) Next declare a variable avg to be equal to the amount remaininf by no of missing elements and change rem to rem modulo n
5) Then initialize a vector res to be of size n and have value avg
6) Then apply for loop and increment res[i]
7) Then return res

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> missingRolls(vector<int>& rolls, int mean, int n) {
        int sum=0;
        for(int i=0;i<rolls.size();i++){
            sum+=rolls[i];
        }
        int rem = (rolls.size() + n) * mean - sum;
        if(rem<n || rem>n * 6) return {};

        int avg= rem/n;
        rem =rem%n;
        vector<int> res(n,avg);

        for(int i=0;i<rem;i++) res[i]++;
        return res;

    }
};
