# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(k), where k is the larger of the length of `rolls` and `n`

- Space complexity: O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int[] missingRolls(int[] rolls, int mean, int n) {
        /** 
        *   the sum of the missing dice rolls  = total - sum of known dice rolls
        *   total = mean * total number of dice rolls (n + rolls.length)
        *   
        **/
        int m = rolls.length;
        int total = mean * (m + n);
        int sum = 0;
        for(int i : rolls) {
            sum += i;
        }
        int missingSum = total - sum;

        /**
        *   get the average value for each missing dice roll
        *   if missingSum > 6n (largest possible sum) OR
        *   if missingSum < 0 OR
        *   if missingSum is not big enough to have an integer value for each missing dice roll
        *   return empty array
        **/
        int avg = missingSum / n;
        int excess = missingSum - avg*n;
        if(missingSum > n * 6 || missingSum < 0 || excess == missingSum) return new int[]{};

        int[] res = new int[n];
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++) {
            res[i] = avg;
        }

        for(int i=0; i<n && excess > 0; i++) {
            res[i] += 1;
            excess--;
        }

        return res;
    }
}
```

